ensive assessment in English of these events. Robert C. Austin first delves into the country&apos;s weak domestic and international position both before and after the First World War, then assesses the internal and external challenges posed to its state- and nation-building efforts. Austin shrewdly demonstrates how the missed opportunities of Albania&apos;s political transition affected the course of Balkan history for decades to come.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aDemocracyzAlbaniaxHistory. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269973140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442699731423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442699731.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK